{
  "texts": [
    "In other words, the integration of AI agents and external resources further blurs the distinction between data and instructions [49].",
    "Indirect Prompt Injection Attack.",
    "Indirect prompt injection attackTo defend against indirect prompt attacks, developers can impose explicit constraints on the interaction between AI agents and external resources to prevent AI agents from executing external malicious data [185].",
    "For example, developers can augment AI agents with user input references by comparing the original user input and current prompts and incorporating self-reminder functionalities.",
    "When user input is first entered, agents are reminded of their original user input references, thus distinguishing between external data and user inputs [14]."
  ]
}